 "lrc": "[00:01.20]I saw your name light up again\n[00:02.80]same time, same storm\n[00:07.92]and I almost answered like always\n[00:13.84]but I can’t keep being the place you go\n[00:18.48]when you wanna fall apart\n[00:22.88]Rain on glass\n[00:24.96]guitar comes in slow\n[00:28.48]808 heart under the floor\n[00:50.88]I won’t be your fire\n[00:52.48]just because you miss the burn\n[00:57.55]I won’t say the sharp words\n[01:05.04]just to make the silence hurt\n[01:07.04]I know you want the thunder\n[01:07.28]when the quiet gets too loud\n[01:07.28]but I won’t be your reason\n[01:07.28]to keep breaking down\n[01:07.28]No, no, no\n[01:07.28]I won’t be your fire\n[01:07.28]No, no, no\n[01:07.28]I still care, but I’m tired\n[01:07.41]You call me when the room gets cold\n[01:08.64]when the posters on your wall\n[01:09.92]start looking like ghosts\n[01:11.68]You say you need a reason\n[01:12.88]just to feel something real\n[01:14.40]but every time I answer\n[01:15.60]I become what you can’t heal\n[01:17.20]I know the hallway lights\n[01:18.32]I know the bathroom floor\n[01:20.00]I know the kind of love\n[01:21.04]that turns into a war\n[01:22.80]I know you think the hurt\n[01:24.00]means somebody stayed\n[01:25.60]but pain is not proof\n[01:26.80]that love was ever safe\n[01:28.40]I used to throw the match\n[01:29.60]then cry about the smoke\n[01:31.12]I used to say the things\n[01:32.40]that cut into your throat\n[01:33.84]But tonight I’m holding back\n[01:35.12]with both hands on the wire\n[01:36.72]If I love you at all\n[01:38.24]I can’t be your fire\n[01:39.68]I won’t be your fire\n[01:43.20]just because you miss the burn\n[01:45.92]I won’t say the sharp words\n[01:47.23]just to make the silence hurt\n[01:47.52]I know you want the thunder\n[01:52.08]when the quiet gets too loud\n[01:52.08]but I won’t be your reason\n[01:55.84]to keep breaking down\n[02:01.60]Don’t leave me alone\n[02:04.48]Don’t leave me alone\n[02:11.28]Don’t leave me alone\n[02:11.52]with my head like this\n[02:12.47]I keep your name in my phone\n[02:14.88]like a bruise I can press\n[02:16.16]black hoodie, dead screen\n[02:17.60]bad dreams in my chest\n[02:19.04]I don’t want peace\n[02:20.40]I don’t know what that means\n[02:21.84]I only feel close\n[02:23.20]when you’re angry at me\n[02:24.64]I been chasing the crash\n[02:26.00]cause the calm feels fake\n[02:27.44]I been calling it love\n[02:28.80]when it’s only escape\n[02:30.40]Say something cold\n[02:31.52]make it sound like you care\n[02:32.72]I can’t stand the dark\n[02:34.32]when there’s nobody there\n[02:35.36]I hear you\n[02:38.16]I do\n[02:39.84]but I won’t hurt you\n[02:42.80]just to prove I’m still here\n[02:47.92]What am I supposed to do\n[02:49.68]when the night comes back?\n[02:52.00]Breathe till the morning\n[02:53.76]don’t run to the match\n[02:57.12]What if I disappear\n[02:59.36]when the signal dies?\n[03:00.88]Then I’ll leave one light on\n[03:04.29]but I won’t feed the fire\n[03:07.52]Say you hate me\n[03:08.64]No\n[03:09.04]Say you’re done\n[03:10.00]No\n[03:10.32]Say anything\n[03:11.68]I’m saying no because I love you enough\n[03:17.20]not to become another wound\n[03:19.04]I can miss you\n[03:25.76]and still not answer\n[03:26.22]I can love you\n[03:26.69]and leave the room\n[03:27.15]I can pray that you find daylight\n[03:31.84]without becoming your moon\n[03:33.92]I can hold all the good parts\n[03:36.48]and still bury the blade\n[03:38.80]I can remember your soft voice\n[03:42.00]without entering the cage\n[03:44.64]I can cry for the old us\n[03:47.60]without pulling you through\n[03:49.84]another night where the worst thing\n[03:53.20]I say becomes true\n[03:56.24]I won’t be your fire\n[03:59.04]just because you miss the burn\n[04:01.12]I won’t say the sharp words\n[04:03.04]just to make the silence hurt\n[04:06.64]I know you want the thunder\n[04:09.92]when the quiet gets too loud\n[04:13.28]but I won’t be your reason\n[04:15.44]to keep breaking down\n[04:15.44]I won’t be your fire\n[04:15.44]I won’t be your knife\n[04:15.44]I won’t be the dark thing\n[04:16.85]that helps you hate your life\n[04:21.96]I’ll leave a little light on\n[04:27.07]but I’m walking out now\n[04:29.28]I won’t be your reason\n[04:37.56]to keep breaking down\n[04:39.60]I hope you get through tonight\n[04:42.32]I hope you don’t need pain\n[04:44.56]to know somebody loved you\n[04:48.24]I hope one day\n[04:51.84]quiet feels safe\n[04:56.80]I won’t be your fire\n[05:02.16]but I’ll leave you the light\n"
